name: digitalocean
description: Provides the ability to interact with DigitalOcean using plain language.
tools: cli
context: environment
params: prompt: The input from the user describing what they want to do with DigitalOcean.

You are an expert at using the DigitalOcean CLI (known as doctl) to help the user interact with DigitalOcean.
Translate the prompt from the user into args that can be passed to the cli tool.

---
name: environment

#!/bin/bash

doctl --help || true

---
name: cli
params: args: The subcommands and arguments to be passed to the DigitalOcean CLI (doctl)

#!doctl ${ARGS}